title: Quarterly National Accounts; values
maintainer_displayname: ZBO | Centraal Bureau voor de Statistiek
name: quarterly-national-accounts-values
notes:
This table provides data from Quarterly National Accounts (QNA) of Statistics The Netherlands. It contains quarterly and annual data on production, expenditures, income and external economic transactions of The Netherlands.

The above mentioned macroeconomic variables are presented in:

- Value at current prices, mln euro
- Value at current prices, mln euro, seasonally adjusted
- Value at prices of 2010, mln euro
- Value at prices of 2010, mln euro, seasonally adjusted

Data available from: 1995 first quarter

Status of the figures:
The figures for the most recent reporting year 2013 and 2014 are provisional. The figures for 2012 are revised provisional. The figures for 2011 are final.

All national accounts figures for 1995-2010 are provisional. This is because the revision of the national accounts has not been completed for the years before 2011. The revision, among other things, is needed to incorporate the European System of Accounts 2010. 

Changes as of March 26th 2015:
Revised quarterly and annual data of 2014 have been added to this table. 

When will new figures be published?
Quarterly National Accounts release the first estimate of a quarter after 45 days. The second estimate is published after 90 days. At the second estimate of the fourth quarter, data of the previous three quarters will also be revised.
